author: Mrs. Tyler Thompson
title: SEC Nation is coming to UK/Tennessee
text:
Posted in Football , Main | 1 Response 
We haven’t seen the SEC Nation guys yet this season, but according to ESPN, they’re coming to our city on October 31 for the Kentucky/Tennessee game. 
They’ll be set up near the purple lot at the intersection of 6th avenue and University Avenue. The show starts at 10 a.m. ET each Saturday and features host Joe Tessitore, analysts Tim Tebow, Marcus Spears and Greg McElroy, as well Paul Finebaum and reporter Kaylee Hartung. 
You ready, Matt? Article written by Mrs. Tyler Thompson No, I will not make you a sandwich, but you can follow me on Twitter @MrsTylerKSR or email me . One response to “SEC Nation is coming to UK/Tennessee” 6th? October 15, 2015 at 12:10 pm | Permalink | Reply
